internalContents.title: * Session Not Invalidated After Logout (16293)
internalContents.description:
Soumya Karnala created:
Summary Session Not Invalidated After Logout
Status New
Description AppScan has found that after a user signs out of the application, the identifiers that were used during the session were not invalidated. If the server fails to invalidate the session identifiers, it is possible for other users to use those identifiers to impersonate that user and perform actions on his behalf.
Authenticating a user, or otherwise establishing a new user session, without invalidating any existing session identifier, gives an attacker the opportunity to steal authenticated sessions.
Such a scenario is commonly observed when:
[1] A web application authenticates a user without first invalidating the existing session, thereby continuing to use the session already associated with the user
[2] An attacker is able to force a known session identifier on a user so that, once the user authenticates, the attacker has access to the authenticated session
[3] The application or container uses predictable session identifiers.
In the generic exploit of session fixation vulnerabilities, an attacker creates a new session on a web application and records the associated session identifier. The attacker then causes the victim to associate, and possibly authenticate, against the server, using that session identifier. This gives the attacker access to the user's account through the active session.

internalContents.title: * 90000 Commission Access (16543)
internalContents.description:
Dinesh Madhavasubramanian created:
Summary  90000 Commission Access
Status New
Description All,

Problem:  90000 agents without the -999 code in their profile cannot access commission statement screen.

My Test:  I had one account “validate”(see attached prod2) that has 90000-028 and 90000-999- This worked fine.  I was to access to statement for only -028 and I tried other statements and it blocked me which is very good.    One problem I saw was that the excel links did not work.

The other account was “EIKOiP6d” and only has 90000-028.(see attached prod1)  I could not get in to commission screen.  I get error seen on error1 attached screenshot.

Background:
When we create agency users the only code they have in Get Access is their corresponding 90000 code – For example 90000-028
I believe the commission statement app has coding that scans for -999 in order to build the drop seen below.  If they don’t they have any -999 it would not allow you in and that’s how we block CISA sub agents.  There was coding added years ago that prevents the user from seeing commission statements if they don’t have the parent code because of a problem we had once when a CISA agent was able to see other statements.


In ST environment the user Vishal tested with “lulucy” has many -999 codes so the system allows you into the commission statement screen and entering a PAS code works fine.  Try to test in ST with an account that only has 90000-028 or any sub code with no other codes that have -999.
